Description: Fragments of papyrus with 8 lines of Demotic text, in black ink on recto, and 12 more on verso. Perhaps part of Book of Fayum, P. Vienna D 10104.
Curator's comments: To be published by Quack. For Book of Fayum see Beinlich, ZAS 126, pl. 3f. Previously unregistered; acquisition and provenance unknown. Originally part of frame EA 76196, which was marked with a biro cross (added by Carol Andrews in connection with demotic?).
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (380695) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/380695)
